headlines.description: Chelsea surged six points clear at the top of the Premier League with a commanding 3-0 win over Leicester on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pulisic scores as Chelsea stay top of Prem table

events.name: Brighton & Hove Albion at Aston Villa

headlines.description: Aston Villa struck late to claim a 2-0 win over Brighton and Hove Albion in the Premier League on Saturday in new boss Steven Gerrard's first match.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gerrard begins Villa era with win over Brighton

headlines.description: — Christian Benteke scored twice and Crystal Palace extended its unbeaten streak to seven games in the Premier League in an entertaining 3-3 draw at Burnley on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Palace extends unbeaten run in 3-3 draw at Burnley

headlines.description: Allan Saint-Maximin rescued a point for Newcastle United in a dramatic 3-3 draw with Brentford on Saturday as new boss Eddie Howe watched on.
headlines.shortLinkText: Heartbreak for Howe as Newcastle drop to last

headlines.description: A glancing Grant Hanley header got the reign of new Norwich boss Dean Smith off to a perfect start as his side beat Southampton 2-1.
headlines.shortLinkText: Smith off to winning start as Norwich beat Saints

headlines.description: Manchester United slumped to a 4-1 defeat to Watford in an action-packed affair on Saturday as pressure grows on manager Ole Gunnar Solskjaer.
headlines.shortLinkText: United thrashed by Watford as Ole gloom grows

events.name: West Ham United at Wolverhampton Wanderers

headlines.description: Wolverhampton Wanderers striker Raul Jimenez netted a fine second-half goal to secure a 1-0 home win over high-flying West Ham United.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jimenez strike gives Wolves 1-0 win over West Ham

headlines.description: — Liverpool handed Arsenal a harsh reality check Saturday by tearing through the Gunners in the second half for a 4-0 win in the Premier League.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rampant Liverpool dismantles Arsenal 4-0 in Premier League
